action and divide by the 1 in its denominator. Next, multiply by 60 in the =
numerator of the third fraction and divide by the 1 hour in its denominator=
. Finally, multiply by the 1 km in the numerator of the last fraction and d=
ivide by the 1000 in its denominator."></p>
                                    <p>11 =F7 1 =D7 60 =F7 1 =D7 60 =F7 1 h=
our =D7 1 km =F7 1000 =3D 39.6 kilometers per hour</p>
                                    <p>So the horse is traveling at a rate =
of <span class=3D"rem1-25"> <mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attach=
